IV Therapy

Intravenous (IV) therapy for many different reasons has been popularized over the past few years.
Results have been impressive in assisting people to receive specific micro nutrients and vitamins in a safe and efficacious manner. Thus, TOKA is pleased to have IV therapy as a service that can partner with our other medical therapies using TOKA CBD.

IV THERAPY MENU

100+ Years

Combined Medical Experience

TOKA is supported with several different physicians and nurses who have a combined medical experience of over 100 years. Thus, the TOKA staff has the ability to help most people with any type of malady.

IV THERAPY MENU

TOKA was created to help people in need of supporting a quality life using various IV drips with appropriate CBD when desired or needed. CBD has been shown to be very effective and supportive of many different problems including help with pain relief, relaxation, boosting of immunity, sleep and several other issues.

IV therapy can be used for hydration only or it can be utilized for the administration of micronutrients to assist in boosting immunity. IV therapy should never be used for the replacement of prescription medications.

Frequently Asked Questions

Down

What is CBD?

CBD, short for cannabidiol, is the non-psychoactive portion of the cannabis plant, cannabis sativa, and it can also be found in the hemp plant. CBD can therefore originate from hemp or a portion of cannabis sativa. CBD is being used currently in medical research for which many medical uses are being found.

Is CBD legal?

In 2018, Congress passed the Agriculture Improvement Act of 2018. In 2019, the act became effective in legalizing hemp or cannabis as long as it contains less than 0.3% of THC (psychoactive portion of cannabis). Thus, the bill removed hemp from the Controlled Substances Act and it expanded hemps commercial cultivation. It made hemp production legal in all US territories.

What are CBD Uses?

CBD has been used effectively for many types of seizure disorders, stress relief, anxiety relief, insomnia, neurodegenerative disorders like multiple sclerosis, Parkinsons disease, Alzheimers disease. CBD can help control inflammatory muscle spasms, pain, and even cancer by preventing cancer cell growth.

CBD is a very effective anti-inflammatory agent, and thereby, it can help with many maladies that cause muscle pain and muscle spasms, skin eruptions and irritability.
